						               													<description>In ACW Solitaire, the player plays the Union forces in the American Civil War of 1861-65. The aim is to defeat a simulated Confederate opponent using a combination of strategies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Units include named Generals, Armies, Forts, River Gunboats, Naval Fleets and different Indian Tribes. The map is province based, including ports and the Mississippi river.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Union victory depends on a series of objectives being achieved, such as cutting the Mississippi and an effective Naval Blockade. It is unlikely the Confederates will win, but it is possible&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has been intensively play tested and should take about an hour to play to completion - offering an exciting and stimulating experience of directing the strategy of the civil war.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are a series of optional rules to allow players to investigate different aspects of the war, including a 2 player version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is a &amp;quot;print and play&amp;quot; game available for US$5 from wargamedownloads.com&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
